### Platform Thread vs Virtual Thread

| | Platform Thread | Virtual Thread ✅ |
|---|---|---|
| **Executor** | `newFixedThreadPool(n)` | `newVirtualThreadPerTaskExecutor()` |
| **Thread creation** | Expensive (OS-level) | Cheap (JVM-managed) |
| **Blocking `sleep()`** | Blocks OS thread | **Unmounts**, frees carrier thread |
| **Scalability** | Limited by thread count | Millions of threads possible |
| **Semaphore still needed?** | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes — controls concurrency limit |

### Why Virtual Threads shine here 💡
```
Platform threads → Thread.sleep() wastes an OS thread doing nothing
Virtual threads  → Thread.sleep() releases the carrier thread back
                   to the pool, which picks up another virtual thread
```
