## ⚠️ One Real Warning: Pinning

```java
// ❌ BAD — This PINS the virtual thread (carrier thread NOT freed)
synchronized (lock) {
    semaphore.acquire();   // blocks inside synchronized = PINNED
}

// ✅ GOOD — Use ReentrantLock instead
ReentrantLock lock = new ReentrantLock();
lock.lock();
try {
    semaphore.acquire();   // safe, unmounts properly
} finally {
    lock.unlock();
}
```

If `semaphore.acquire()` is called **inside a `synchronized` block**, the virtual thread gets **pinned** to its carrier thread — defeating the purpose of virtual threads.

---

## Summary

| Scenario | Carrier Thread Freed? |
|---|---|
| `semaphore.acquire()` waiting | ✅ Yes — unmounts via `LockSupport.park()` |
| `Thread.sleep()` waiting | ✅ Yes |
| `synchronized` block blocking | ❌ No — **pinned** |
| `ReentrantLock` blocking | ✅ Yes |

So your `ConcurrencyLimiter` with `Semaphore` + Virtual Threads is **correctly efficient** as written! 🚀
